# Cursor Rules — TTS Web App

> **This is the canonical rules file.** Product spec: `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-12-tts-web-app-prd.md`. For questions about product, read the PRD. For dev rules, read this file.

## Project Overview
Text-to-speech web app. Users paste text or upload files, select a voice, convert to MP3.

## Task Tracking
- Read `TASKS.md` for the current build checklist
- Follow the phase and task order in `TASKS.md` strictly. Do not suggest skipping phases or doing tasks out of order (e.g. Phase 3 before Phase 2). Respect dependencies: later phases often depend on outputs of earlier phases.
- After completing each task: describe how to test it, then ask if the user wants you to update `TASKS.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and push to GitHub. Do not update or push until the user confirms.
- When confirmed: mark task `[x]` in `TASKS.md`, add one-line summary to `CHANGELOG.md`, commit and push.

## Architecture (2 layers)
1. **Frontend:** React + Tailwind CSS + Shadcn UI → deployed to Vercel
2. **Backend + GPU:** Python / FastAPI + Chatterbox Multilingual → all on Modal (serverless)

There is NO separate backend service. Modal hosts everything: the API (via `@modal.asgi_app()`), file parsing, chunking, TTS generation, and audio stitching. The stack is just Vercel + Modal.

## Critical Rules

### Modal (Backend API + GPU Worker)
- Serve the FastAPI app using `@modal.asgi_app()` on Modal.
- Use CPU functions for lightweight work: file parsing, chunking, progress tracking, serving files.
- Use GPU functions for heavy work: Chatterbox TTS generation and audio stitching (pydub + ffmpeg).
- Process chunks **sequentially** in the same GPU container. Do NOT use `.starmap()` or `.map()` across containers — each container reload costs 30–60s and causes jobs to hang.
- Stitch all audio chunks into a single MP3 on the GPU function. Return only the final MP3.
- Install ffmpeg and pydub in the Modal image.
- Voice reference clips are bundled in the Modal image.
- Use PyMuPDF (`import fitz`) for PDF parsing. Do NOT use PyPDF2.
- Reference: https://modal.com/docs/examples/chatterbox_tts

### Frontend (React)
- Use Tailwind CSS + Shadcn UI. Shadcn provides components; Tailwind provides utilities. No other CSS framework.
- Warm & friendly design: soft colors, rounded corners, approachable feel.
- Single page app, no routing needed.
- Voice cards: horizontal row on desktop, vertical stack on mobile.
- Poll backend every 2 seconds for progress during conversion.
- Show "Warming up..." during Modal cold start before progress percentage kicks in.

### Text Processing
- Chunk text at ~300 characters, splitting at sentence boundaries (not mid-word).
- Maximum 20,000 words. Validate on both frontend (word counter) and backend.
- Maximum file upload size: 10 MB.
- Supported file types: .txt, .pdf only.

### Error Handling
- Follow error messages exactly as specified in the PRD error handling table.
- Retry failed chunks up to 3 times silently before showing an error to the user.

### Testing
- After any change to `modal_app/main.py`, write a pytest test for it in `modal_app/tests/` and confirm it passes before marking the task done.
- Backend tests are more valuable than frontend tests — all the real processing happens there.
- Focus on: route responses (`/convert`, `/job/{id}/status`), `chunk_text()` edge cases (blank lines, `\r\n`, empty input, long text), and the full job lifecycle (submit → poll → complete).

### Code Style
- Python: use type hints, async where appropriate, follow PEP 8.
- TypeScript/React: functional components, hooks, no class components.
- Keep files focused — one component per file, one endpoint group per router file.
- No over-engineering. MVP only. Do not add features not in the PRD.

## Known Pitfalls

### Chatterbox TTS
- Import: `from chatterbox.tts import ChatterboxTTS` — NOT `chatterbox.tts_turbo` (that module does not exist)
- Call `model.prepare_conditionals(voice_path)` **once** before the chunk loop, not inside it — calling it per-chunk causes the GPU to hang on the second chunk
- Install numpy before chatterbox-tts in the Modal image (pkuseg has a build isolation issue that requires numpy to already be present)

### Modal Deploy
- Always run `modal deploy` from the **project root**, not from inside `modal_app/` — the `voices/` directory is resolved relative to where you run the command
- After every deploy, sanity-check: hit `/health`, submit a short text job, poll until complete

## Assistant Operational Rules

- Whenever a change requires restarting the **backend** (Modal app) to take effect, the assistant should:
  - Explicitly state that a redeploy is needed, **and**
  - Automatically run `python3 -m modal deploy modal_app/main.py` from the project root, rather than asking the user to do it.
- Whenever a change requires restarting the **frontend dev server** for local testing, the assistant should:
  - Explicitly state that a restart is needed, **and**
  - Automatically start or restart `npm run dev` in the `frontend` directory, rather than asking the user to do it.

